and%20rally.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jsor%40businessinsider.com%20(Jennifer%20Sor)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-sp500-prediction-bull-rally-morgan-stanley-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20laid%20off%20in%20my%2060s%20and%20can't%20find%20a%20job%20after%2011%20months.%20I%20wish%20I%20could%20retire%2C%20but%20I%20can't%20afford%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robin%20Daniel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1a868a96e437d6eb8237f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22660%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERobin%20Peppers%20Daniels%20pivoted%20to%20substitute%20teaching%20after%20Wells%20Fargo%20laid%20her%20off.%3Cp%3ERobin%20Daniel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERobin%20Peppers%20Daniel%20was%20laid%20off%20by%20Wells%20Fargo%20last%20April.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20finding%20work%20in%20her%2060s%20has%20been%20a%20struggle%2C%20but%20she%20can't%20afford%20to%20retire%20yet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20turned%20to%20substitute%20teaching%20post-layoff%20and%20is%20now%20exploring%20full-time%20teaching%20opportunities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Robin%20Peppers%20Daniel%2C%20a%20job%20seeker%20in%20her%20early%2060s%20who%20lives%20in%20South%20Carolina.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20April%2C%20I%20received%20a%20notification%20that%20I%20had%2030%20minutes%20before%20I%20would%20lose%20all%20of%20my%20work%20access%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20within%20an%20hour%2C%20I%20would%20receive%20some%20paperwork.%20Then%20my%20boss%20called%20me%20with%20the%20news%3A%20I%2C%20along%20with%20several%20colleagues%2C%20had%20been%20laid%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20working%20for%20Wells%20Fargo%20in%20a%20management%20role%2C%20and%20had%20some%20suspicion%20that%20a%20layoff%20was%20coming.%20This%20wasn't%20my%20first%20layoff.%20In%202018%2C%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-cutting-roles-remove-layers-complexity-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elaid%20off%20from%20Walmart%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20I%20worked%20as%20an%20instructional%20design%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20little%20over%20a%20year%20later%2C%20I%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwells-fargo-hiring-spree-investment-bankers-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%20for%20Wells%20Fargo%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20external%20regulatory%20reporting%20consultant%20and%20was%20later%20promoted%20to%20a%20lead%20control%20management%20officer%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20last%20working%20day%20at%20Wells%20Fargo%20was%20in%20April%2C%20but%20I%20was%20technically%20still%20employed%20and%20received%20paychecks%20through%20mid-June%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20few%20months%20of%20severance.%20Nearly%20a%20year%20after%20being%20laid%20off%2C%20I'm%20still%20looking%20for%20a%20full-time%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224b8ab3ed-a5db-43dc-9205-6faffae8fd46%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20search%20strategies%20haven't%20landed%20me%20a%20role%20so%20far%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20some%20reorganization%20about%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20there%20was%20redundancy%20in%20certain%20areas%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20like%20my%20workload%20started%20to%20dry%20up.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20start%20financially%20preparing%2C%20which%20proved%20to%20be%20beneficial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20already%20been%20casually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-job-search-white-collar-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elooking%20for%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20partially%20because%20I'd%20felt%20for%20a%20while%20that%20the%20role%20wasn't%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20me.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20until%20I%20was%20laid%20off%20that%20I%20updated%20my%20LinkedIn%20profile%2C%20and%20not%20until%20around%20June%20that%20I%20began%20actively%20searching%20for%20roles.%20I%20was%20initially%20focused%20on%20banking%20and%20corporate%20trainer%20roles%2C%20but%20I've%20become%20open%20to%20any%20position%20where%20my%20skills%20are%20transferable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-search-strategies-whether-application-hacks-actually-work-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20search%20strategies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20adopted%20the%20%26quot%3Bopen%20to%20work%26quot%3B%20banner%20on%20LinkedIn%20and%20posted%20that%20I%20was%20seeking%20work%2C%20which%20helped%20me%20connect%20with%20people%20who%20said%20they'd%20be%20open%20to%20referring%20me%20for%20roles.%20I've%20also%20tried%20looking%20for%20job%20postings%20on%20company%20websites%20rather%20than%20only%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20where%20I've%20found%20that%20some%20postings%20can%20be%20outdated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20strategies%2C%20I%20was%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-youre-not-getting-hired-job-interview-resume-advice-tips-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estruggling%20to%20land%20a%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20was%20one%20opportunity%20last%20year%20that%20I%20thought%20might%20work%20out.%20I%20had%20a%20referral%20from%20a%20former%20coworker%20who%20said%20she'd%20spoken%20about%20me%20to%20the%20hiring%20manager.%20After%20three%20interviews%2C%20I%20waited%20several%20weeks%20and%20eventually%20heard%20they%20were%20going%20in%20another%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20speaking%20with%20workers%20who've%20found%20themselves%20at%20a%20corporate%20crossroads%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20due%20to%20a%20layoff%2C%20resignation%2C%20job%20search%2C%20or%20shifting%20workplace%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSechTVqVWQve8iqYssNriCXdtwwdgGRixNNZpmslSKBQqIJ8g%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dheader%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efilling%20out%20this%20form%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contacting%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20via%20Signal%20at%20jzinkula.29.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5e49822-b24b-4619-8eb7-96886832ca44%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20pick%20up%20substitute%20teaching%20shifts%20when%20I%20can%2C%20but%20I'm%20still%20unemployed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20have%20enough%20savings%20to%20be%20financially%20stable%20for%20roughly%20the%20next%2018%20months.%20In%20a%20perfect%20world%2C%20I%20would%20retire%20and%20get%20out%20of%20this%20work%20rat%20race%2C%20but%20right%20now%2C%20I%20unfortunately%20can't%20afford%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20August%2C%20I%20applied%20to%20be%20a%20substitute%20teacher%20in%20my%20area%20so%20I%20could%20have%20some%20form%20of%20income%20once%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-file-for-unemployment-benefits-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emy%20unemployment%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20ran%20out.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20used%20to%20substitute%20teach%20when%20my%20daughter%20was%20preschool%20age%2C%20and%20I%20enjoyed%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20I%20had%20to%20be%20very%20strategic%20about%20taking%20on%20substitute%20work.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-midwest-to-charleston-south-carolina-family-benefits-living-here-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elive%20in%20South%20Carolina%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20worked%20in%20North%20Carolina%20%E2%80%94%20and%20was%20therefore%20subject%20to%20that%20state's%20unemployment%20system.%20In%20North%20Carolina%2C%20you%20can%20earn%20a%20maximum%20of%20%24350%20a%20week%20in%20unemployment%20benefits%20for%20up%20to%2012%20weeks%20%E2%80%94%20%244%2C200%20total.%20You%20can%20also%20earn%20up%20to%20%2470%20a%20week%20without%20impacting%20your%20unemployment%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20full%20week%20of%20substitute%20teaching%20paid%20about%20%24550%2C%20and%20depending%20on%20how%20many%20days%20I%20was%20needed%2C%20I%20had%20to%20make%20sure%20what%20I'd%20gain%20in%20income%20would%20offset%20what%20I'd%20lose%20that%20week%20in%20unemployment%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22256f6332-5b43-48cf-a80f-2e5a420b00dd%5C%22%3EI'm%20now%20considering%20teaching%20full-time%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20pursuing%20an%20alternative%20teaching%20pathway%20in%20South%20Carolina%20that%20would%20eventually%20allow%20me%20to%20work%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F92-work-full-time-not-ready-retire-teacher-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efull-time%20teacher%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20initial%20testing%20is%20complete.%20The%20salary%20wouldn't%20be%20what%20I%20earned%20in%20banking%2C%20but%20it%20would%20allow%20me%20to%20do%20something%20that%20I%20enjoy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20also%20started%20exploring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearn-extra-money-with-these-21-high-paying-side-jobs-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epart-time%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20hopefully%20provide%20me%20with%20income%20and%20benefits%2C%20including%20a%20small%20web%20design%20business%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20have%20run%20for%20years%20and%20a%20small%20skincare%20products%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb266b36-8cff-431e-84e5-d1d4f09fa832%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20realized%20this%20could%20be%20a%20really%20long-term%20unemployment%20spell%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20much%20of%20my%20job%20search%2C%20I%20was%20fairly%20optimistic%20because%20I'd%20previously%20found%20full-time%20jobs%20through%20my%20network.%20Over%20time%2C%20I've%20realized%20that%20I%20could%20be%20unemployed%20for%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20my%20age%20might%20be%20holding%20me%20back%20in%20my%20job%20search%2C%20and%20that%20some%20employers%20view%20me%20as%20overqualified%2C%20given%20my%20past%20work%20experience%20and%20education.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20I've%20been%20conscious%20of%20the%20way%20I%20present%20and%20talk%20about%20my%20experience%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowadays%2C%20I'm%20only%20half-heartedly%20looking%20for%20full-time%20work.%20If%20a%20job%20posting%20has%20more%20than%20100%20applicants%2C%20I%20don't%20apply.%20I've%20resigned%20myself%20to%20semi-retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20have%20any%20advice%20for%20struggling%20job%20seekers%2C%20it's%20that%20tapping%20into%20my%20network%20and%20family%20has%20been%20the%20biggest%20help%20for%20me%2C%20even%20if%20it%20hasn't%20led%20to%20a%20job%20yet.%20I've%20had%20some%20former%20coworkers%20%E2%80%94%20more%20acquaintances%20than%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20reach%20out%20to%20tell%20me%20about%20jobs.%20I%20really%20believe%20that%20in%20this%20market%20%E2%80%94%20where%20AI%20might%20be%20the%20one%20reviewing%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20all%20about%20networking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-wells-fargo-job-search-retirement-savings-unemployment-teaching-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773306661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1a875a7a4f9df67ba2a39%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-wells-fargo-job-search-retirement-savings-unemployment-teaching-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20Wells%20Fargo%20laid%20off%20R