80%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22headshot%20of%20a%20woman%20on%20a%20gray%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1a01ca7a4f9df67ba293d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDiana%20Choi.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Diana%20Choi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDiana%20Choi%20found%20peace%20and%20stability%20by%20moving%20back%20in%20with%20her%20parents%20after%20burning%20out%20abroad.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELiving%20at%20home%20helped%20Choi%20save%20money%2C%20aiding%20the%20launch%20of%20her%20K-beauty%20brand%2C%20Vibes%20of%20Grace.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChoi's%20decade%20at%20home%20has%20both%20strengthened%20family%20ties%20and%20supported%20her%20entrepreneurial%20journey.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20conversations%20with%20Diana%20Choi%2C%20a%2039-year-old%20founder%20in%20Vancouver%2C%20Canada.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20I%20graduated%20and%20moved%20to%20New%20York.%20I%20spent%20the%20year%20interning%20and%20then%20attending%20graduate%20school%20at%20The%20New%20School.%20After%20finishing%20my%20program%20in%20September%202011%2C%20I%20began%20working%20at%20the%20Asia%20Society%2C%20a%20global%20nonprofit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20realizing%20the%20path%20wasn't%20the%20right%20fit%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-hong-kong-moved-home-england-expat-networking-starting-over-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoved%20to%20Hong%20Kong%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20work%20for%20Lane%20Crawford%2C%20one%20of%20the%20region's%20largest%20luxury%20retailers.%20It%20looked%20glamorous%2C%20but%20I%20burned%20out%2C%20so%20I%20resigned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%202016%2C%20I%20had%20just%20turned%2030%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20Asia.%20My%20dad%20suggested%20I%20come%20home%20to%20Vancouver%20to%20regroup%20and%20restore%20my%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20short-term%20reset%2C%20but%20I'm%20still%20here%2C%2010%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202de3203-a623-4a4b-a3c2-a6f1c126f2b0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuddenly%2C%20I%20was%2030%2C%20living%20at%20home%20again%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20clear%20sense%20of%20what%20I%20wanted%20next.%20At%20first%2C%20the%20shift%20from%20an%20extremely%20fast-paced%20life%20to%20a%20slower%20one%20felt%20like%20relief.%20My%20mental%20and%20physical%20health%20improved.%20Over%20time%2C%20that%20stillness%20began%20to%20feel%20like%20stagnation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20three%20months%20off%2C%20I%20got%20antsy%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanalyst-quit-jpmorgan-to-run-restaurants-with-father-best-decision-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejoined%20my%20dad's%20medical%20distribution%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20traveled%20with%20him%20for%20about%20two%20years%2C%20all%20the%20while%20searching%20for%20other%20job%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20recommend%20living%2C%20working%2C%20and%20traveling%20with%20your%20parents.%20I%20felt%20like%20he%20treated%20me%20like%20a%20child%2C%20almost%20like%20an%20intern%2C%20and%20wouldn't%20let%20me%20make%20important%20decisions.%20I%20had%20been%20in%20a%20managerial%20role%20in%20Asia%2C%20leading%20teams%20and%20projects.%20That%20disconnect%20was%20probably%20why%20I%20ultimately%20decided%20to%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2293eca41e-d2db-4d12-9120-2e787e6f0018%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDespite%20the%20challenges%2C%20there%20were%20unexpected%20upsides%20to%20living%20at%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20as%20a%20business%20development%20consultant%20for%20a%20luxury%20concept%20store%20and%20briefly%20served%20as%20a%20marketing%20communications%20manager%20for%20two%20separate%20Canadian%20tech%20companies.%20These%20jobs%20have%20helped%20me%20contribute%20financially%20to%20household%20expenses.%20I%20help%20cover%20groceries%20and%20shared%20costs%2C%20including%20our%20monthly%20cleaning%20service%20and%20auto%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20financial%20flexibility%20and%20being%20able%20to%20be%20selective%20about%20the%20opportunities%20I%20say%20yes%20to%2C%20it's%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fhow-to-calm-anxiety%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egiven%20me%20a%20much%20calmer%20nervous%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20together%20as%20adults%20healed%20parts%20of%20my%20relationship%20with%20my%20parents%2C%20especially%20as%20they've%20gotten%20older.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphillips-exeter-academy-changed-life-wouldnt-send-kids-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleft%20home%20for%20boarding%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2016%2C%20so%20I'd%20never%20spent%20extended%20time%20as%20an%20adult%20with%20them.%20The%20past%20decade%20gave%20me%20that%2C%20and%20it%20taught%20me%20patience%20and%20compromise%2C%20skills%20I%20think%20will%20come%20in%20handy%20one%20day%20when%20I%20cohabitate%20with%20someone%20and%20start%20my%20own%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20bonus%20is%20the%20comfort%20of%20knowing%20that%20the%20house%20will%20always%20be%20clean%20and%20neat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a232bbc0-bedd-451c-af4e-a890b8882cb1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20definite%20trade-offs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20curfew%2C%20and%20it%20feels%20like%20a%20personal%20regression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20with%20parents%20as%20an%20adult%20can%20be%20emotionally%20and%20socially%20challenging%3A%20being%20treated%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bchild%26quot%3B%20again%2C%20navigating%20boundaries%2C%20and%20dating%20have%20been%20complicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20men%20I've%20dated%20didn't%20mind%3B%20others%20questioned%20it%20openly%2C%20and%20in%20at%20least%20one%20case%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20dealbreaker.%20On%20dates%2C%20my%20mom%20would%20call%20me%20at%20midnight%20and%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20are%20you%20coming%20home%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c693983-d897-4331-a831-3f70b03f5ce2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20haven't%20found%20many%20high-paying%20jobs%20in%20Vancouver%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20making%20much%20money%20is%20why%20I've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-back-with-parents-save-money-bonded-over-shared-hobby-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estayed%20at%20home%20longer%20than%20planned%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20that%20flexibility%20ultimately%20gave%20me%20the%20space%20to%20start%20my%20own%20consulting%20business%20for%20beauty%20and%20lifestyle%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20that%20business%20grew%2C%20giving%20me%20the%20confidence%20and%20runway%20to%20start%20building%20my%20consumer%20brand%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvibesofgrace.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVibes%20of%20Grace%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20K-beauty%20brand%20for%20people%20with%20sensitive%20and%20reactive%20skin%2C%20which%20I'm%20fully%20self-funding.%20I've%20been%20able%20to%20save%20around%20%2470%2C000%20across%20investments%2C%20business%20savings%2C%20and%20retirement%20contributions%20by%20living%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20an%20entrepreneur%2C%20you're%20constantly%20navigating%20uncertainty%2C%20risk%2C%20and%20decision%20fatigue.%20Having%20something%20steady%2C%20like%20a%20consistent%20routine%20and%20a%20solid%20home%2C%20has%20been%20grounding%20for%20me.%20It%20gives%20me%20a%20sense%20of%20peace%20and%20stability%2C%20helping%20me%20stay%20focused%20and%20perform%20better%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263e1b0f6-e04c-4aa7-bd23-0191c8c345f6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20entering%20my%2040s%20soon%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20keep%20living%20with%20my%20parents%20forever%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHopefully%2C%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20I'll%20move%20out%2C%20depending%20on%20how%20the%20brand%20launch%20goes.%20Ten%20years%20feels%20like%20a%20good%20moment%20to%20enter%20a%20new%20chapter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20feel%20embarrassed%20about%20living%20at%20home%20for%20so%20long.%20I%20don't%20anymore.%20As%20a%20founder%20and%20entrepreneur%2C%20I%20now%20see%20it%20as%20a%20privilege%20that%20gave%20me%20the%20freedom%20to%20be%20selective%2C%20take%20risks%2C%20and%20build%20something%20aligned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-back-with-parents-30-still-here-39-pros-cons-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773306302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1a15ea96e437d6eb8229f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-back-with-parents-30-still-here-39-pros-cons-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20woman%20in%20Vancouver%20has%20saved%20%2470%2C000%20and%20started%20her%20own%20business%20by%20living%20with%20her%20parents%20through%20her%2030s.%20She%20plans%20to%20move%20out%20this%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kaila%20Yu)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-back-with-parents-30-still-here-39-pros-cons-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Big%20Law's%20outlaw%20has%20something%20to%20prove%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226837%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Max%20Junestrand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b08272ccda166eed3d1e92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225470%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMax%20Junestrand.%3Cp%3EMartynas%20Justinevicius%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESilicon%20Valley%20loves%20a%20rivalry%2C%20and%20right%20now%20one%20of%20its%20most%20closely%20watched%20showdowns%20is%20unfolding%20in%20an%20unlikely%20arena%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fin-house-legal-tech-ai-cost-cutting-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecorporate%20law%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvey%20and%20Legora%2C%20two%20artificial-intelligence%20startups%20selling%20software%20to%20law%20firms%2C%20are%20jockeying%20for%20customers%2C%20credibility%2C%20and%20bragging%20rights.%20With%20this%20week's%20news%20that%20Legora%20raised%20%24550%20million%20in%20an%20investment%20round%20valuing%20the%20company%20at%20%245.5%20billion%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flegora-first-acquisition-and-the-great-legal-tech-rollup-continues-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquired%20the%20startup%20Walter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Sweden-based%20company%20is%20one%20step%20closer%20to%20challenging%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvey-legaltech-fund-legal-tech-startups-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHarvey's%20dominance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMax%20Junestrand%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmax-junestrand-legora-founder-legal-tech-ai-harvey-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELegora's%2026-year-old%20wunderkind%20founder%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20no%20legal%20training%2C%20isn't%20going%20to%20settle%20for%20runner-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20video-calls%20me%20from%20a%20bare%20Stockholm%20apartment%20that%20he%20hasn't%20had%20time%20to%20furnish%2C%20he%20mentions%20that%20he's%20coming%20off%20a%2072-hour%2C%20100-degree%20fever%2C%20and%20it's%20blunted%20his%20usual%20zip.%20Still%2C%20he's%20serious%20about%20his%20mantra.%20%26quot%3BWe%20try%20to%20operate%20like%20elite%20swimmers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Btrained%20to%20look%20down%20and%20swim%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20look%20at%20the%20sidelines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20Legora%20tells%20itself%20internally%2C%20the%20competition%20is%20playing%20out%20in%20public.%20Even%20their%20board%20members%20have%20joined%20the%20spectacle%2C%20trading%20barbs%20online%20over%20which%20company%20is%20pulling%20ahead.%20In%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fgradypb%2Fstatus%2F2016609435108683879%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20exchange%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Sequoia%20partner%20Pat%20Grady%20argued%20there%20was%20no%20contest%2C%20saying%20Harvey%20added%20more%20revenue%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20than%20any%20competitor%20has%20in%20total.%20Legora's%20chairman%2C%20Benchmark's%20Chetan%20Puttagunta%2C%20jeered%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20lady%20doth%20protest%20too%20much%2C%20methinks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investor%20sparring%20is%20the%20beef's%20public%20version.%20The%20private%20version%20happens%20in%20conference%20rooms%2C%20where%20lawyers%20still%20have%20to%20be%20convinced%20to%20trust%20software%20with%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Harvey-Legora%20clash%20is%20more%20than%20startup%20theater.%20It's%20a%20high-stakes%20proxy%20war%20for%20how%20quickly%20AI%20can%20impact%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20more%20conservative%20industries.%20As%20billions%20of%20venture%20dollars%20flood%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftltf-summit-lawyers-use-ai-legal-tech-industry-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egenerative%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rival%20founders%20and%20their%20investors%20are%20racing%20not%20just%20for%20customers%2C%20but%20for%20proof%20that%20AI%20can%20crack%20the%20professional%20services%20economy.%20Legal%20services%20alone%20hit%20%241%20trillion%20in%20revenue%20worldwide%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20Precedence%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20these%20head-to-head%20combats%20are%20increasingly%20defining%20the%20AI%20era%3A%20fast%20followers%20challenging%20early%20leaders%2C%20VCs%20publicly%20staking%20claims%2C%20and%20customers%20buying%20more%20than%20one%20product%20because%20no%20one%20is%20sure%20who%20will%20lead%20six%20months%20from%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20days%20of%20Legora%2C%20Junestrand%20cold-messaged%20lawyers%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20offering%20to%20pay%20their%20hourly%20rate%20for%20a%20meeting.%20He's%20since%20channeled%20his%20charisma%20into%20the%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20just%20a%20fireball%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Michael%20Gerstenzang%2C%20a%20senior%20partner%20at%20Cleary%20Gottlieb%2C%20one%20of%20the%20marquee%20firms%20using%20Legora.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224257%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Max%20Junestrand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b0824cccda166eed3d1e8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223406%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20Harvey%20showed%20that%20large%20language%20models%20could%20be%20packaged%20into%20software%20lawyers%20would%20actually%20use%2C%20Legora%20is%20betting%20it%20can%20out-execute%20the%20early%20market%20leader.%3Cp%3EMartynas%20Justinevicius%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20paper%2C%20though%2C%20the%20Harvey-Legora%20matchup%20is%20pretty%20one-sided.%20Forbes%20reports%20Harvey%20could%20be%20worth%20%2411%20billion%20in%20a%20new%20fundraise.%20In%20the%20scramble%20for%20Big%20Law's%20business%2C%20the%20competition%20looks%20already%20won.%20Of%20the%20100%20highest-grossing%20law%20firms%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Legora%20says%20it%20counts%20about%2020%25%20of%20them%20as%20customers.%20Harvey%20has%20more%20than%20half%20of%20these%20firms%20using%20its%20software.%20Legora%20won't%20share%20its%20revenue%2C%20while%20Harvey%20says%20last%20year%20it%20booked%20about%20%24190%20million%20in%20annual%20recurring%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20the%20income%20a%20company%20collects%20from%20subscription%20fees%20over%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Harvey%20showed%20that%20large%20language%20models%20could%20be%20packaged%20into%20software%20lawyers%20would%20actually%20use%2C%20Legora%20is%20betting%20it%20can%20out-execute%20the%20early%20market%20leader.%20Over%20the%20last%20year%2C%20Legora%20has%20increased%20its%20customers%20from%20250%20to%20800%2C%20and%20became%20the%20fastest%20startup%20out%20of%20the%20famed%20Silicon%20Valley%20startup%20incubator%20Y%20Combinator%20to%20reach%20unicorn%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20%26quot%3B20VC%26quot%3B%20podcast%20recently%2C%20Junestrand%20described%20his%20competitive%20point%20of%20view%3A%20%26quot%3BThere's%20only%20winning.%20Everything%20else%20is%20losing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegora%20arrived%20after%20Harvey%20and%2C%20at%20first%2C%20built%20a%20familiar%20kind%20of%20virtual%20paralegal.%20Now%20Junestrand%20argues%20the%20roles%20are%20reversing%20and%20competitors%20are%20copying%20Legora's%20features.%20He%20doesn't%20name%20names%2C%20but%20Harvey%20launched%20a%20client-facing%20portal%20about%20a%20month%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flegal-ai-startup-legora-client-portal-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELegora%20rolled%20out%20its%20own%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20Junestrand%2C%20that's%20not%20a%20threat%2C%20but%20confirmation%20that%20Legora%20is%20starting%20to%20set%20the%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BImitation%20is%20the%20sincerest%20form%20of%20flattery%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Legora's%20first%20board%20meeting%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20when%20the%20company%20had%20about%2012%20employees%2C%20Junestrand%20made%20a%20surprising%20announcement.%20He%20told%20his%20investors%20that%20Legora%20would%20not%20sell%20its%20product%20at%20all%20for%20the%20next%20six%20months.%20Junestrand%20explained%20that%2C%20since%20Harvey%20was%20already%20in%20the%20market%2C%20Legora%20had%20to%20bring%20an%20excellent%20product.%20If%20they%20delivered%20a%20demo%20that%20wasn't%20fully%20baked%2C%20they%20would%20%26quot%3Bburn%20that%20one%20shot%26quot%3B%20with%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reaction%20in%20the%20boardroom%20was%20mixed.%20The%20company%20had%20just%20raised%20%2435%20million.%20Halting%20sales%20right%20after%20a%20round%20was%20a%20risk%2C%20one%20that%20looked%20like%20it%20would%20starve%20Legora%20of%20the%20early%20customer%20love%20that%20it%20needed%20to%20compete.%20Still%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexclusive-legal-ai-startup-leya-raising-new-round-redpoint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBenchmark's%20Puttagunta%3C%2Fa%3E%20firmly%20believed%20that%20a%20company%20doesn't%20need%20to%20be%20the%20first%20to%20market%20as%20long%20as%20it%20is%20the%20best.%20History%20tends%20to%20reward%20that%20kind%20of%20execution%3A%20Google%20eclipsed%20Yahoo%3B%20Uber%20outran%20Lyft.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20other%20investors%20agreed%2C%20and%20the%20team%20spent%20the%20next%20few%20months%20retooling%20the%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20just%20the%20specter%20of%20Harvey%20that%20Legora%20had%20to%20overcome.%20Not%20long%20ago%2C%20selling%20any%20new%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esoftware%20to%20law%20firms%20looked%20like%20a%20losing%20business.%20Lawyers%20lived%20in%20documents.%20Before%20large%20language%20models%2C%20software%20was%20lousy%20at%20pulling%20data%20it%20could%20read%20from%20messy%20text%2C%20which%20meant%20most%20%26quot%3Blegal%20tech%26quot%3B%20tools%20could%20only%20search%20documents%20by%20keywords.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20other%20limitations.%20Lawyers%20have%20long%20bristled%20at%20the%20idea%20of%20machines%20doing%20their%20work.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskadden-david-goldschmidt-retires-career-advice-ai-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EClients%20pay%20for%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20bespoke%20advice%2C%20and%20for%20the%20human%20who%20will%20stand%20behind%20a%20call%20when%20it%20goes%20sideways.%20More%20practically%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-impact-billable-hour-lawyers-legal-world-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebillable%20hour%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20fuels%20law%20firms'%20coffers%20made%20efficiency%20unattractive.%20Software%20that%20saves%20time%20can%20also%20shrink%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20a%20firm%20can%20charge%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225358%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Max%20Junestrand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b082a4ccda166eed3d1e9b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226697%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELegora%20is%20rigidly%20in-person%2C%20five%20days%20a%20week.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20know%20what%20we're%20going%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Junestrand%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhy%20don't%20we%20do%20it%20today%3F%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EMartynas%20Justinevicius%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20large%20language%20models%20landed%20four%20years%20ago%2C%20suddenly%20the%20tech%20could%20do%20something%20that%20earlier%20tools%20couldn't%3A%20read%2C%20summarize%2C%20and%20rewrite%20legalese%20in%20plain%20English.%20This%20sent%20up%20a%20signal%20flare%20that%20even%20the%20most%20change-averse%20of%20industries%20could%20actually%20be%20disrupted%20by%20this%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20Junestrand%2C%20along%20with%20his%20cofounders%20Sigge%20Labor%20and%20August%20Ers%C3%A9us%2C%20began%20sketching%20out%20an%20idea%20for%20a%20new%20startup.%20It%20would%20do%20what%20lawyers%20do%3A%20comb%20through%20data%20rooms%20for%20red%20flags%2C%20compare%20contracts%2C%20research%2C%20and%20draft%20briefs.%20If%20it%20worked%2C%20Junestrand%20reasoned%2C%20the%20company%2C%20then%20called%20Leya%2C%20stood%20to%20become%20the%20central%20platform%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20all%20legal%20work.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhat%20Figma%20is%20to%20designers%20and%20Salesforce%20is%20to%20sales%20reps%2C%20Legora%20would%20be%20to%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJunestrand%20didn't%20look%20like%20the%20guy%20to%20tell%20elite%20lawyers%20how%20they%20should%20work.%20He%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20Stockholm%20archipelago%2C%20where%20his%20mother%20worked%20in%20pharma%2C%20and%20his%20father%20owned%20a%20boat%20business.%20He%20taught%20himself%20English%20by%20grinding%20through%20%26quot%3BWorld%20of%20Warcraft%26quot%3B%20quests%2C%20bought%20a%20sailboat%20at%2016%2C%20and%20even%20modeled%20briefly%20as%20a%20teen%2C%20appearing%20on%20posters%20around%20Stockholm%20advertising%20an%20ABBA%20museum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20modeling%20career%20did%20not%20last%20very%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20grinning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJunestrand%20juggled%20courses%20at%20the%20prestigious%20KTH%20Royal%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20and%20Sweden's%20top%20business%20school%20while%20working%20full-time%20in%20venture%20capital.%20It%20only%20worked%20because%20the%20pandemic%20pushed%20classes%20online%2C%20though%20he%20eventually%20dropped%20out%20of%20KTH%20to%20focus%20on%20Legora.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Legora's%20profile%20rose%2C%20so%20did%20Junestrand's.%20He%20prophesied%20the%20end%20of%20the%20billable%20hour%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftbpn-dove-deep-sportscenter-silicon-valley-tech-bros-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etech-friendly%20talk%20show%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BTBPN%2C%26quot%3B%20made%20the%20Forbes%2030%20Under%2030%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fmaxjunestrand_yesterday-i-had-the-opportunity-to-meet-activity-7396927528776421376-OB-b%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehobnobbed%20with%20the%20French%20president%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20talk%20about%20European%20technical%20ambition.%20Junestrand%20now%20splits%20his%20time%20between%20Stockholm%20and%20New%20York%2C%20becoming%20a%20kind%20of%20emissary%20for%20Sweden's%20Silicon%20Valhalla.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20Friday%20afternoon%2C%20I%20stopped%20by%20Legora's%20office%20just%20south%20of%20Union%20Square.%20Patrick%20Forquer%2C%20the%20executive%20in%20charge%20of%20revenue%2C%20led%20me%20past%20rows%20of%20empty%20desks%20to%20the%20kitchen%20for%20a%20LaCroix.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20employees%20hunched%20over%20monitors%20as%20lo-fi%20beats%20thumped%20from%20a%20speaker.%20Most%20workers%2C%20Forquer%20explains%2C%20were%20on%20the%20road%20trying%20to%20win%20over%20firms.%20Otherwise%2C%20Legora%20is%20rigidly%20in-person%2C%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20he%20says%2C%20on%20the%20belief%20that%20the%20most%20important%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-from-home-surviving-return-to-office-mandates-era-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ework%20happens%20live%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20together.%20To%20keep%20people%20around%2C%20catered%20dinners%20arrive%20at%208%20p.m.%20in%20the%20Stockholm%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForquer%20said%20the%20selling%20part%20is%20relatively%20easy.%20Right%20now%2C%20many%20law%20firms%20feel%20they%20have%20to%20at%20least%20look%20fluent%20in%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20because%20corporate%20clients%20are%20asking%20what%20tools%20they're%20using.%20Gerstenzang%2C%20the%20Cleary%20Gottlieb%20lawyer%2C%20views%20the%20pressure%20as%20an%20existential%20threat.%20He%20warns%20that%20if%20top-tier%20firms%20don't%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20do%20the%20routine%20work%20better%2C%20faster%2C%20and%20cheaper%20using%20technology%2C%20clients%20will%20simply%20take%20that%20work%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20tell%20me%20their%20firms%20are%20buying%20licenses%20to%20many%20platforms%2C%20keeping%20their%20options%20open.%20Clients%20may%20arrive%20with%20preferences%20about%20their%20firm's%20tech%2C%20and%20partners%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20locked%20into%20a%20tool%20that%20could%20look%20second-rate%20months%20from%20now.%20As%20one%20law-firm%20executive%20put%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20in%20the%20fortunate%20position%20that%20we%20now%20have%20the%20Coke%20and%20Pepsi%20of%20our%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20law%20firms%20pour%20money%20into%20new%20tools%2C%20many%20still%20can't%20say%20what%20they're%20getting%20back.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvey-legal-ai-roi-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20on%20the%20investment%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20up%20in%20lawyers%20moving%20faster%20and%20less%20busywork.%20What's%20harder%20is%20turning%20that%20into%20something%20a%20managing%20partner%20can%20point%20to%20on%20a%20financial%20report%20or%20a%20client%20bill.%20That%20raises%20questions%20about%20how%20long%20firms%20will%20keep%20paying%20for%20%26quot%3Bnice%20to%20have%26quot%3B%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJunestrand%20knows%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvey-legaltech-fund-legal-tech-startups-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emarket%20is%20just%20getting%20started%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20no%20lead%20is%20stable.%20If%20Legora%20can%20take%20market%20share%20from%20Harvey%2C%20another%20company%20can%20do%20the%20same%20to%20Legora.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20playing%20the%20infinite%20game%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amrussell%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Emrussell%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20%40MeliaRussell.01.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20non-work%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehere's%20our%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-